Former New England Patriots tight end Aaron Hernandez was moved Wednesday to Souza-Baranowski Correctional Center in Shirley, Massachusetts .
Hernandez was sentenced to life in prison for killing 27-year-old Odin Lloyd in 2013 .
The prison is about ten minues from Fort Devens, where Boston Marathon bomber Dzhokhar Tsarnaev was held for the last two years .
It houses more than 1,000 inmates, many of whom are serving life sentences .